  "slug": "slab-built-oval-planter",
  "title": "Slab-built oval planter",
  "subtitle": "A four-wall slab planter with a drainage insert, sealed for outdoor shelf use",
  "excerpt": "A medium oval planter built from five clay slabs (four walls and a base) with an inner drainage insert to keep the outer clay body dry. Sealed air-dry clay survives a sheltered outdoor spot; an inner terracotta or plastic pot handles water. Intermediate difficulty because of accurate corner joining.",
  "type": "PATTERN",
  "sourceNotes": "Slab-building technique derived from first principles.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A slab-built planter uses the same construction logic as the lidded box but scaled up and shaped for a decorative outer pot. The key principle: air-dry clay is not waterproof, so the outer clay planter holds a smaller terracotta or plastic inner pot that handles all the watering. The clay body stays dry.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "suppliesCard",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Air-dry clay",
              "quantity": "350 g",
              "substitution": "Paper clay for stronger corners"
            },
            {
              "name": "Pottery rolling pin",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "6 mm guide rails",
              "quantity": "1 pair",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Fettling knife",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Needle tool",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Inner nursery pot to use as reference",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            }
          ],
          "heading": "What you need"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cutting the pieces",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "slabs",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpe36s030000swv4s0l4c11n"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " to 6 mm thickness. Cut the following pieces to fit a 13 cm by 10 cm inner nursery pot (adjust to match your inner pot):",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Base: 15 cm by 12 cm",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Two long walls: 15 cm by 12 cm",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Two short walls: 12 cm by 12 cm (each adds 6 mm for wall thickness)",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assembly",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "1. Join the walls to the base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Use ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "score-and-slip",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpe36xah0000hgv4cnsr37ur"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " on every join. Stand the long walls on the base first. Then fit the short walls into the open ends. Reinforce all interior corners with thin coils pressed flat with a rib.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "2. Add texture to the exterior",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "While the walls are still soft, press stamps, a leaf, or coarse linen into the exterior faces for texture.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "3. Add drainage feet",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll four short cylinders of clay, each 8 mm diameter and 15 mm tall. Score and slurry the base of the planter at the corners and press a cylinder foot at each corner. These raise the planter off the shelf for drainage and airflow.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drying and sealing",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let the assembled planter firm to ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "leather-hard",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpb7rmoo00008gv4xfq393tk"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " under light plastic cover, then dry open for two to three days. Once bone-dry, apply three coats of exterior-grade acrylic varnish or PVA, covering all surfaces including the base. Three coats provides enough water resistance for a sheltered outdoor position.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Care",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Keep the outer planter dry: water the plant through the inner pot only. Bring indoors during heavy rain or frost. Air-dry clay, even sealed, is not suitable for full outdoor exposure.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": null,
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Press paper clay slurry into the crack; allow to dry slowly",
              "cause": "Corners were not reinforced with coils or score-and-slip was skipped",
              "symptom": "Corners split after drying"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Weight the base with a flat ceramic tile while drying; or dry upside-down on the base so the base dries last",
              "cause": "Base dried faster than the walls",
              "symptom": "Base bows upward during drying"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "Planter problems"
        }
      }
    ]
